suming you're still using those two weapons. <p><html><body><big><b>-<a href=http://www.suckbird.com/roster/profile.asp?who=Iskandar>Isk</a></b></big></body></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukaldayrmalabranche.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaldayr Malabranche</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 218<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 10:16:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1782.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: whats better to use?</span><hr size=1> Considering I'm using a Silver Sword of Yalrek at 60... you may still be using them : P    (hoping to get epics next week, we'll see... so close)<br><br>pre-45ish, it doesn't matter as much which one you have where (although faster weapon in primary hand will usually generate more agro regardless because it has more opportunity to swing)<br><br>post-45ish, putting the faster weapon in primary hand matters more because your damage bonus becomes significant.<br><br>There is *no* damage bonus at all on any 1h weapon before level 28, at which point you gain a 1 point bonus and it increased by 1 point every 3 levels to a max of 11 at 58. <p><IMG SRC="http://users.starpower.net/dmoser/images/warlord.jpg" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=200></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/con's RED</span><br>  Posts: 305<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 4:44:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1782.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: whats better to use?</span><hr size=1> At your level it doesnt matter what you use. There is a damage cap until level 20 anyway so you might as well be using fine steel weapons. You really can't take advantage of the fast 1 hand weapons until you get a decent damage bonus and that won't be until level 40+. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial"><img src="http://www.bfdesigns.net/eq/wandor_sig.jpg"><br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor's profile</b></a> | <a target="_blank" href="http://www.exarch.net/"><b>Fusion of Flame</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102" target="_blank"><b>Moordian's profile</b></a></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uveganondeadlyblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veganon Deadlyblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 5:41:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1782.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: whats better to use?</span><hr size=1> Fast weapons help a lot at low lvls.  I have many lvl10-20 alts that are melee classes too.  Fast weapons = fast skill raising... taking less damage while soloing because the mob dies faster.  <br><br>But, back to the question... I would put the Lammy in main and Silver Sword of the Yalrek in offhand at my lvl... but at your's it would be better damage with the Yalrek in main, because in low lvl groups... or soloing you're not worried about maintaining aggro. A lot of people won't even understand the concept because they could be new to the game.  Besides, low lvl mobs only care about who's hitting them the hardest, they're not worried as much about who's swinging at them the fastest. <p><p><table bordrer=0 width=300 bgcolor=#000000><tr><td align=center ><img width=280 height=143 src="http://www.nhbzone.com/up4it/up4it_images/Veganonsiggy4.jpg"></td><tr><td align=center> <a style="color:red; font-weight:bold" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=54849">My Profile</a> <a style="color:white; font-weight:bold" href="http://silverdaggers.freehosting.net">Silver Daggers</a> <span style="color:blue; font-weight:bold">Karana Server</span> </td></table></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uveganondeadlyblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veganon Deadlyblade</A> at: 2/8/02 5:43:34 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uranorny.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ranorny</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/02 11:36:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1782.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   thanks</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the help guys, i do appreciate it <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showPrevMessage?topicID=1782.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <